TITLE: Swedish EV maker Polestar reports lower operating loss, confirms full-year guidance
SUMMARY: Cost cuts and higher sales helped EV maker Polestar trim its operating loss from a year ago. The company expects to deliver 50,000 vehicles in 2022.

TITLE: Nio reports strong third-quarter revenue as it gears up for a big year-end production push
SUMMARY: Nio's loss widened significantly from a year ago, but revenue was strong, and the company guided to a big jump in production in the fourth quarter.

TITLE: Rocket Lab reports record quarterly revenue, with added contract wins
SUMMARY: Rocket Lab delivered quarterly results on Wednesday that boasted record revenue, with the space company tacking on additional contract wins across its business.

TITLE: Rivian seeks to cut costs while boosting EV production to meet 2022 targets
SUMMARY: Rivian said it now has "over 114,000" preorders for its R1-series trucks and SUVs.

TITLE: Beyond Meat reports wider-than-expected loss, falling revenue
SUMMARY: Beyond Meat reported a wider-than-expected loss as demand for its meat substitutes tumbled.

TITLE: Roblox shares sink after reporting bigger loss than expected
SUMMARY: Shares of Roblox fell in premarket trading Wednesday after the company reported a third-quarter loss but beat analyst estimates for revenue.

TITLE: Adidas warns of big earnings hit after ending Ye partnership
SUMMARY: Adidas on Wednesday cut its full-year guidance on the back of the German sportswear giant's termination of its partnership with Kanye West's Yeezy brand.

TITLE: Disney misses on profit and key revenue segments, warns streaming growth could taper
SUMMARY: Disney fell short of expectations for profit and key revenue segments during the fiscal fourth quarter Tuesday.

TITLE: Electric vehicle maker Lucid reports third-quarter loss, confirms it's on track to meet production guidance
SUMMARY: The company said it's still on track to make between 6,000 and 7,000 of its luxury sedans this year.

TITLE: Novavax posts third quarter loss but beats revenue expectations
SUMMARY: The Covid-19 vaccine maker reported a net loss of more than $169 million for the third quarter, compared to a loss of $322 million in the same period last year.

TITLE: Lyft shares fall after disappointing revenue, active rider miss
SUMMARY: Lyft reported third-quarter revenue that fell short of estimates, and active riders came in below Wall Street's forecast.

TITLE: Take-Two stock tumbles after it cuts outlook
SUMMARY: Take-Two's slashed outlook comes as gaming is a fast cooling businesses after two years of elevated sales and engagement thanks to the Covid-19 pandemic.

TITLE: Palantir stock falls after slight earnings miss
SUMMARY: Shares of Palantir fell Monday after the company released third-quarter earnings that slightly missed analyst estimates for earnings but beat on revenue.

TITLE: Berkshire Hathaway's operating earnings jump 20%, conglomerate buys back another $1 billion in stock
SUMMARY: Berkshire Hathaway posted a solid gain in operating profits during the third quarter despite rising recession fears.

TITLE: DraftKings shares tumble after monthly users fall short of estimates
SUMMARY: DraftKings stock fell as much as 26% on Friday despite the sports betting company posting higher-than-expected revenue for its third-quarter earnings report.

TITLE: Carvana tumbles after posting declines in nearly every aspect of the car reseller's business
SUMMARY: Shares of Carvana fell in extended trading Thursday after the online used car retailer missed Wall Street's top- and bottom-line expectations for the third quarter.

TITLE: DoorDash stock surges after sales beat expectations
SUMMARY: DoorDash reported better-than-expected sales and total orders for the third quarter.

TITLE: Paypal drops on light revenue forecast for Q4
SUMMARY: PayPal shares fell more than after hours despite beat on earnings and revenue expectations for the third quarter.

TITLE: Starbucks U.S. sales climb as customers spend more on pricey drinks
SUMMARY: Shares of Starbucks have fallen nearly 28% this year, dragging its market value down to $97.11 billion.

TITLE: Atlassian plummets more than 20% on weak earnings report and disappointing forecast
SUMMARY: Atlassian's free users are also converting to paid customers more slowly.

TITLE: Coinbase reports better-than-expected user numbers even as third-quarter revenue plunges
SUMMARY: Coinbase has struggled this year as cryptocurrency prices have plunged and investors have rotated out of the riskiest assets.

TITLE: Shares of Block jump on earnings beat
SUMMARY: Block stock rose in extended trading after the payments company reported third-quarter earnings that beat Wall Street expectations for profit.

TITLE: Twilio shares plunge 34% on light guidance
SUMMARY: Twilio is taking steps to be more efficient in its operations as it aims at adjusted operating profitability in 2023. Layoffs are a part of that effort.

TITLE: Warner Bros Discovery reports underwhelming revenue, says new streaming service coming earlier
SUMMARY: Warner Bros. Discovery reported third quarter earnings and said its merged HBO Max-Discovery+ streaming service will come in spring instead of summer.

TITLE: Altice USA stock sinks after tough third quarter earnings
SUMMARY: Altice USA's stock sunk more than 20% Thursday after a weak earnings report

TITLE: Nikola cuts production guidance, sending stock down despite strong earnings report
SUMMARY: Nikola trimmed its production guidance for the full year and declined to provide guidance for 2023.

TITLE: Peloton shares tumble after company offers weak holiday quarter outlook
SUMMARY: Peloton reported a wider-than-expected loss and a steeper decline in revenue than analysts projected, while offering a weak holiday-quarter outlook.

TITLE: Restaurant Brands' earnings top estimates as sales rise at Burger King, Tim Hortons
SUMMARY: Restaurant Brands reported quarterly earnings that beat analysts' expectations, fueled by sales growth at Burger King and Tim Hortons.

TITLE: Qualcomm shares fall on first-quarter guidance, hiring freeze announced
SUMMARY: Qualcomm shares fell in extended trading on Wednesday after the chipmaker offered poor first-quarter guidance.

TITLE: Etsy shares pop on revenue beat, rosy guidance
SUMMARY: Etsy posted better-than-expected sales for the third quarter, and gave a rosy forecast for the current quarter.
